      "role": "user",
      "content": "it felt way more physical than just \"intuition\" though. it was like a specific pitch that didn't match the words he was saying, almost like a micro-tonal dissonance. if i focus on it, i can actually map out the tremor in the sound. do you think there could be a physical or acoustic reason why a lie would actually change the way a person's voice resonates?",
