      "content": "That level of detail, focusing on micro-tonal dissonance, suggests a very keen ear for vocal harmonics. When a person is stressed or trying to mask a deeper emotion like dishonesty, it can cause subtle, involuntary changes in their vocal cord tension and breath control. These physical tensions can indeed alter the natural resonance and pitch stability of their voice, leading to the type of \"tremor\" you're describing. This is a fascinating intersection of psychology and acoustics.",
